title: Laranjeiras Esporte Clube
text:
Laranjeiras Esporte Clube, commonly known as Laranjeiras, is a Brazilian <a href="Association%20football">football</a> club based in <a href="Laranjeiras%2C%20Sergipe">Laranjeiras</a>, <a href="Sergipe">Sergipe state</a>.
History.
The club was founded on February 22, 2008. Laranjeiras reached the semifinal stage of the <a href="Campeonato%20Sergipano%20%28lower%20levels%29">Campeonato Sergipano Série A2</a> in 2009, when they were eliminated by <a href="Riachuelo%20Futebol%20Clube">Riachuelo</a>.
Stadium.
Laranjeiras Esporte Clube play their home games at <a href="Est%C3%A1dio%20An%C3%ADbal%20Franco">Estádio Aníbal Franco</a>. The stadium has a maximum capacity of 3,000 people.
